# Employee Attrition Prediction Using Decision Trees

## Overview

This project demonstrates the complete machine learning workflow for predicting employee attrition using a Decision Tree Classifier. Using the IBM HR Employee Attrition dataset, the project covers data exploration, preprocessing, feature engineering, model training, and performance evaluation. The objective is to identify employees who are likely to leave the organization, enabling HR departments to make informed retention decisions.

## Business Problem

Employee turnover is costly and can negatively affect an organization's productivity and performance. This project aims to develop a predictive model that identifies employees at risk of attrition based on demographic, job-related, and workplace characteristics.

## Project Objectives

* Explore and understand the employee attrition dataset.
* Clean and preprocess the data for machine learning.
* Encode categorical variables into numerical features.
* Split the data into training and testing datasets.
* Build a Decision Tree classification model.
* Evaluate model performance using accuracy, confusion matrix, precision, recall, and F1-score.
* Interpret the model to understand the factors influencing employee attrition.

